'''Alexander Nicholas "Alex" Bono''' (born April 25, 1994) is an American [[Association football|soccer]] player who currently plays as goalkeeper for [[Toronto FC II]], on loan from [[Toronto FC]].

== Career ==

=== College and amateur ===

Born and raised in [[Baldwinsville, New York]], Bono attended high school at [[Charles W. Baker High School]] where he was a two-year starter for the Bees. During the latter years of his high school career, Bono opted to commit full-time to Empire United. Prior to college, Bono was seen as the top goalkeeper recruit in the state of New York, and the 51st highest prospect of his graduating high school class.

Joining [[Syracuse University]], Bono became the immediate starter for the [[Syracuse Orange men's soccer]] program, starting in playing in 20 matches in freshman season, becoming the first true freshman goalkeeper to start a season opener since [[Robert Cavicchia]] in 2005. During his freshman year, Bono recorded a career high eight saves during the [[2012 NCAA Division I Men's Soccer Championship|2012 NCAA Division I Men's Soccer Tournament]] against the [[VCU Rams men's soccer|VCU Rams]] on November 18, 2012 and equalled that tally on November 25 against the [[Georgetown Hoyas men's soccer|Georgetown Hoyas]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Orange Stun #19 VCU, 3-2|url=http://cuse.com/news/2012/11/18/MSOC_1118125217.aspx|website=Syracuse University Athletics|publisher=Cuse.com|accessdate=January 18, 2015}}</ref> During his freshman season, Bono was voted to the [[Big East Conference]] All-Rookie Team, and was named the Orange's Rookie of the Year.

In Bono's sophomore year, he maintained similar statistics as his freshman year, and was named to the [[Atlantic Coast Conference]] Third Team. 

It was his junior year where Bono emerged as a potential professional prospect, as he helped the Orange earn top national rankings, and earn a ninth overall seed in the [[2014 NCAA Division I Men's Soccer Championship|2014 NCAA Division I Men's Soccer Tournament]]. In the tournament, the Orange reached the fourth round before being eliminated by Georgetown.<ref>{{cite web|title=Rist's Game Winner Sends Hoyas to Elite 8|url=http://www.guhoyas.com/sports/m-soccer/recaps/113014aaa.html|publisher=GUHoyas.com}}</ref>  Bono was also named a first-team [[All-American]] by the [[NSCAA]] in 2014.<ref>http://www.nscaa.com/awards/2014-ncaa-division-i-men-s-all-america-teams?utm_medium=short_url</ref>

=== Professional ===
On January 15, 2015, Bono was selected 6th overall by [[Toronto FC]] in the [[2015 MLS SuperDraft]]. He was considered to the be the highest prospective goalkeeper in the draft class.<ref>{{cite web|title=Toronto FC selects Alex Bono with sixth pick in MLS SuperDraft|url=http://www.torontofc.ca/news/2015/01/toronto-fc-selects-alex-bono-sixth-pick-mls-superdraft|website=Toronto FC|publisher=Torontofc.ca|accessdate=January 18, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Former Syracuse and Baldwinsville goalie Alex Bono selected sixth overall in MLS Draft|url=http://www.syracuse.com/orangesports/index.ssf/2015/01/former_syracuse_soccer_goalie_alex_bono_selected_no_6_overall_in_mls_draft_by_to.html|publisher=Syracuse.com}}</ref>

Bono was loaned to [[Toronto FC II]] on March 20, 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.torontofc.ca/news/2015/03/toronto-fc-loan-seven-players-toronto-fc-ii|title=Toronto FC loan seven players to Toronto FC II|date= March 20, 2015}}</ref>  He made his debut against the [[Charleston Battery]] on March 21.<ref>{{cite web|first=Kamal|last=Hylton|date=March 21, 2015|title=Match Recap: TFC II vs. Charleston|url=http://www.torontofc.ca/news/2015/03/match-recap-tfc-ii-vs-charleston}}</ref>

=== International ===
On January 9, 2015, Bono was called into a training camp for the [[United States men's national soccer team]], becoming the second collegiate player since the foundation of MLS to be called into national team camp.<ref>{{cite web|title=Klinsmann Calls 28 Players for First Training Camp of 2015|url=http://www.ussoccer.com/stories/2015/01/09/11/46/150109-mnt-january-camp-roster-rel|publisher=USSoccer.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=USMNT Profile: Alex Bono<U+2019>s rise to his first US call-up|url=http://prosoccertalk.nbcsports.com/2015/01/22/usmnt-profile-alex-bonos-rise-to-his-first-us-call-up/|publisher=NBCSports.com}}</ref>

